titleStmt.title: Kormáks saga according to AM 132 fol : A digital edition

publicationStmt.date: Converted from database and adapted to Menota, 25 September 2020.

msIdentifier.msName: Kormáks saga according to AM 132 fol (Möðruvallabók)

msContents.p: OEH: Description of the contents of the manuscript may be added here

origin.p: This manuscript was written in Iceland c. 1330-1370.

projectDesc.p: This manuscript text has been encoded according to the standard set out in ........ (OEH: can be specified with reference to a version of the Menota Handbook)

normalization.p: This manuscript text has been encoded on three levels: facsimile, diplomatic and normalised.

correction.p: ALW: Verses are not yet lemmatized and analyzed .
OEH: Comments on the correction may be added here.

interpretation.p: That is true for the prose text, but the verses are not yet done.
Words missing in the manuscript text and added by the editor are neither lemmatized nor morphologically analyzed.
Headings were not included in the original database, but have been added in this version in all 3 versions and have been lemmatized and analyzed.

Verses have been added to the database in all 3 versions. Lemmatization and morphological analysis is provisional in the first verse and not yet done in the other 82 verses. This will probably need the help of an expert in skaldic verse.
